.Dd April 4, 2026
.Dt 9X 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm 9x
.Nd a window manager inspired by Plan 9's rio
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl v
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a minimalist X11 window manager inspired by Plan 9's rio.
It provides reparenting window management with 4-pixel borders,
10 virtual desktops, a built-in status bar, an application launcher
with incremental search, and an Alt-Tab window switcher.
.Pp
Windows are managed with a combination of mouse gestures on borders
and keyboard shortcuts.
All keyboard shortcuts use
.Ic Alt
(Mod1) as the modifier.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl v
Print version and exit.
.El
.Sh MOUSE BINDINGS
.Ss Root Window and Status Bar
Clicking on the root window (desktop background) or the status bar:
.Bl -tag -width "Button 4/5"
.It Button 1
Open the window menu (list of windows on the current desktop).
.It Button 2
Open the desktop menu (list of virtual desktops).
.It Button 3
Sweep a new terminal: hold and drag to define the window geometry,
then release.
The terminal command is defined by the
.Dv TERM
constant (default:
.Ic xterm ) .
.It Button 4/5
Cycle to the previous/next virtual desktop.
.El
.Ss Window Menu
The window menu lists all windows on the current desktop.
Different mouse buttons perform different actions on the selected entry:
.Bl -tag -width "Button 3"
.It Button 1
Focus and raise the selected window, closing the menu.
.It Button 2
Kill the selected window.
The menu stays open and updates to reflect the remaining windows,
allowing multiple windows to be killed in succession.
.It Button 3
Re-sweep (reshape) the selected window using the sweep gesture.
The window is focused and raised first, then the menu closes and
the sweep begins.
.El
.Ss Window Borders
Clicking on a window's border initiates a resize operation.
The border is divided into directional zones
(N, S, E, W and diagonal corners)
with corresponding resize cursors.
.Bl -tag -width "Button 3"
.It Button 1
Resize the window by dragging the border.
A red outline shows the new geometry.
Release to apply.
.Pp
During a resize, additional chords are available:
.Bl -tag -width "Button 3"
.It Button 2
Cancel the resize and re-sweep (reshape) the window freely.
.It Button 3
Cancel the resize and delete (close) the window.
.El
.It Button 2
Toggle maximize.
A maximized window fills the screen minus borders.
.It Button 3
Move the window by dragging.
A red outline shows the new position.
.El
.Ss Inside Client Windows
.Bl -tag -width "Alt+Button 3"
.It Button 1
Focus and raise the window (click-to-focus).
.It Alt+Button 1
Resize the window from the bottom-right corner.
.It Alt+Button 3
Move the window.
.El
.Sh KEYBOARD BINDINGS
All keyboard bindings use
.Ic Alt
(Mod1) as the modifier unless otherwise noted.
.Bl -tag -width "Alt+Shift+Space"
.It Alt+Return
Spawn a new terminal (centred, default size).
.It Alt+Space
Open the application launcher.
The selected program is spawned at the default position and size.
.It Alt+Shift+Space
Open the application launcher in sweep mode.
After selecting a program, drag to define its window geometry.
.It Alt+Tab
Open the window switcher.
Press Tab repeatedly to cycle through windows on the current desktop.
Release Alt to focus the selected window.
Shift+Tab cycles backwards.
Escape cancels.
.It Alt+q
Close (delete) the focused window.
If the window supports WM_DELETE_WINDOW, a delete message is sent;
otherwise the client is killed.
.It Alt+m
Toggle maximize on the focused window.
.It Alt+F11
Toggle fullscreen on the focused window.
A fullscreen window covers the entire screen including the status bar
and has no borders.
.It Alt+1 No ... Alt+0
Switch to virtual desktop 1\(en10.
.It Alt+Shift+1 No ... Alt+Shift+0
Send the focused window to virtual desktop 1\(en10.
The window is unmapped from the current desktop and becomes the
focused window on the target desktop.
.It Alt+Left
Switch to the previous virtual desktop.
.It Alt+Right
Switch to the next virtual desktop.
.El
.Sh APPLICATION LAUNCHER
The application launcher is a full-screen-width menu that appears at the
top of the screen (when invoked via keyboard) or at the cursor position
(when invoked from a menu).
It indexes all executables in
.Ev PATH
and provides incremental substring filtering as you type.
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "Ctrl+u"
.It Type
Filter the list by substring match.
.It Return
Launch the selected (highlighted) program, or the typed text if no
match is highlighted.
.It Tab
Complete the input with the currently selected item.
.It Backspace
Delete the last character.
.It Ctrl+u
Clear the input.
.It Ctrl+n , Down
Select the next item.
.It Ctrl+p , Up
Select the previous item.
.It Escape
Cancel.
.El
.Sh STATUS BAR
A small status bar is displayed in the bottom-right corner of the screen.
It shows:
.Bl -bullet
.It
The current virtual desktop number in brackets (e.g.\&
.Ic [1] ) .
.It
Battery percentage and AC status on supported platforms
(OpenBSD via
.Xr apm 4 ,
FreeBSD via
.Ic hw.acpi ) .
An exclamation mark prefix indicates the system is on battery power.
.It
The current time formatted according to the
.Dv TIMEFMT
constant (default:
.Ic %H:%M %a %d/%m ) .
.El
.Pp
The bar refreshes every 60 seconds and always stays above normal windows
unless a window is fullscreened.
.Sh VIRTUAL DESKTOPS
.Nm
provides 10 virtual desktops numbered 1 through 10.
Each desktop maintains its own focus state.
Windows can be moved between desktops with
.Ic Alt+Shift+N
or viewed by switching with
.Ic Alt+N .
Scrolling (Button 4/5) on the root window or bar also cycles desktops.
.Sh SWEEP GESTURE
The sweep gesture, inherited from rio, allows precise placement and sizing
of new windows.
Press and hold a mouse button to set the origin corner, drag to the
opposite corner to define the rectangle, and release.
A red outline is drawn during the drag.
If the resulting rectangle is too small, the operation is cancelled.
.Sh CUSTOMIZATION
.Nm
is customized by editing constants in the source code and recompiling.
Notable tunables include:
.Bl -tag -width "COL_*"
.It Dv COL_*
Color definitions for borders, menus, bar, and root background.
.It Dv BORDER
Border width in pixels (default: 4).
.It Dv CORNER
Corner zone size for diagonal resizing (default: 25 pixels).
.It Dv MOD
Modifier key (default: Mod1Mask / Alt).
.It Dv XFTFONT
Font for menus and the window switcher.
.It Dv BARFONT
Font for the status bar.
.It Dv TERM
Terminal emulator command (default: xterm).
.It Dv NDESKS
Number of virtual desktops (default: 10).
.It Dv TIMEFMT
.Xr strftime 3
format string for the bar clock.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr X 7 ,
.Xr xterm 1
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Toby Slight
.Sh BUGS
.Nm
does not support EWMH/ICCCM beyond the minimum required for basic
window management (WM_PROTOCOLS, WM_DELETE_WINDOW, WM_TAKE_FOCUS,
WM_STATE).
Some applications that depend on extended hints may not behave correctly.